The White House announced that 7,041,000 people signed up for health insurance before the March 31 deadline. This number does not include the last-day surge in signups in more than a dozen states that run their own marketplaces. The article also mentions that the law has reduced the percentage of uninsured Americans and slowed the growth of healthcare costs. The White House emphasizes that the law is a success because it provides good, affordable coverage to millions of Americans and eliminates discrimination against preexisting conditions. However, the article acknowledges that the law still faces opposition from Republicans and that there is more work to be done to improve the healthcare system.